                <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aius</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Curi</abbr><ex>us</ex></expan> Placi<lb break="no" n="2"/>dus <expan><abbr>an</abbr><ex>norum</ex></expan> XX <expan><abbr>h</abbr><ex>ic</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>itus</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>e</abbr><ex>st</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aius</ex></expan> Curius Valeriu<lb break="no" n="4"/>s <expan><abbr>vet</abbr><ex>eranus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>leg</abbr><ex>ionis</ex></expan> XV <expan><abbr>Ap</abbr><ex>ollinaris</ex></expan> et <lb n="5"/>Cavia Nice posue<lb break="no" n="6"/>runt <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilio</ex></expan> suo et <lb n="7"/>sibi
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Zeile 3: U klein am Zeilenende. Im Hauptbild oberhalb des Inschriftfeldes Adler in Kranz, flankiert von Genien und Säulen. Reste von roter Farbe in den Buchstaben. (B): Z. 5: Vorbeck: C(aia) Nice bzw. Caia Avia in der Übersetzung des Inschriftentextes; Mosser: C(aia) Avia Nice. (C): Datierung: 1./2. Jh.</p>
            </div>
